<div style>Dear all,</div>
<div style><br />
</div>
<div style>I have a problem with openmpi1.3, ifort&#43;mkl v11.1 in Ubuntu10.04 systems (32 or 64bit). My code worked in Ubuntu8.04 and works in RedHat based systems, with slightly different version changes on mkl and ifort.&nbsp;There were no changes in the source
 code.</div>
<div style>The problem is that the application works for small cell sizes per core, but not for large cell sizes per core. And it always works for 1 core.&nbsp;</div>
<div style>Example: a grid with 1.2Million cells does not work with mpiexec -n 4 &lt;my_app&gt; but it works with mpiexec -n 32 &lt;my_app&gt;.&nbsp;It seems that there is a maximum of cell/core. And it works with &lt;my_app&gt;.</div>
<div style><br />
</div>
<div style>Is this a stack size (or any memory problem)? Should I set the ulimit -s unlimited not only on my bashrc but also in the ssh environment (and how)? Or is something else?</div>
<div style>Any clues/tips?</div>
<div style><br />
</div>
<div style>Thanks for any help.</div>
<div style><br />
